# English Words - Streamlit App

## 📌 Live Demo
🔗 [English Words - Streamlit App](https://datageniesk-english-words-english-words-wxfkyw.streamlit.app/)

## 📂 Project Repository
🔗 [GitHub Repository](https://github.com/DatagenieSK/english_words)

## 📖 About the Project
This Streamlit app generates five random English words daily and provides their meanings using the **NLTK WordNet** database. It ensures that each word is randomly picked from a predefined word list and maintains session state to track previous words.

## 🚀 Features
- Generates **five new words** daily.
- Provides **definitions** using the WordNet database.
- Saves and retrieves the **word state** using JSON files.
- **Interactive UI** using Streamlit.

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- **Python**
- **Streamlit** (for UI)
- **NLTK** (for word definitions)
- **JSON & OS** (for data storage)

## 📑 Installation Guide
### 1️⃣ Clone the Repository
```sh
git clone https://github.com/DatagenieSK/english_words.git
cd english_words
```

### 2️⃣ Install Dependencies
Ensure you have Python **3.7+** installed. Then run:
```sh
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3️⃣ Download NLTK Data
Run the following in Python to download the WordNet dataset:
```python
import nltk
nltk.download('wordnet')
```

### 4️⃣ Run the Streamlit App
```sh
streamlit run app.py
```

## 📜 File Structure
```
english_words/
│-- app.py              # Main Streamlit app
│-- word_list.txt       # List of words for the app
│-- word_state.json     # Stores shuffled words & progress
│-- requirements.txt    # Dependencies
│-- README.md           # Project documentation
```

